    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-02-05T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-02-05T15:00:00-05:00" n="699"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d699">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/8920: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in France, to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perpignan</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-02-05T20:00:00+00:00"
                            >February 5, 1939—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 6—8:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1206. Best information available indicates that complete collapse has occurred in
                    Catalan area, and that rebel forces probably are now in Figueras. President
                    Azana was seen here this morning and is reported to be in Paris. Negrin is said
                    to have reached Madrid area.</p>
                <p>It also is reported that all restrictions have been removed at border and that
                    Loyalist forces will be permitted to enter France throughout the night for
                    internment. 85,000 refugees are understood to have entered France already and
                    arrival of remnants of army will probably raise this figure to about
                    125,000.</p>
                <p>Alvarez del Vayo is expected to come to Perpignan tonight and I shall endeavor to
                    see him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
